MissionCommands.Message: Welcome to the Apollo 11 Flight Plan mission. Follow the Mission Details document in the (AOH) Command Module checklists tab, along with the real flight plan (Flight Documents (SHIFT+M) -> Apollo 11 documents).
[Complete the TIMELINE -> Pre-Launch: Launch Preparations Checklists]
[Follow the TIMELINE -> Ascent: Boost checklist (PAGE L/2-7) ]
[The deflecting angle (Z-torquing) angle will be plus 0.22 for the P52 alignment.]
[Complete the TIMELINE -> Insertion: Post Insertion and System Checks (Item 1 - 31, PAGE L/2-11)]
[ Preparing TLI data and PAD. ]
[ Open TLI planner and plan a TLI burn at GET ~002:44:26 (TB6 ~002:34:48) to reach a Lunar Pe of 60 nmi alt, etimated LOI at GET ~075:54:28 ]
[ Start TLI PREPARATION (PAGE L/2-27) and complete the burn. ]
[ Burn complete, proceed with the checklist. S-IVB will maneuver to sep attitude at 003:05:00. S-IVB sep planned at 003:15:00. ]
[ Verify and Activate RCS DAP R1=11103, R2=01111 ]
[ S-IVB maneuvering to sep attitude.]
[ Complete the TIMELINE -> T&D: PRE CSM SEPARATION PREP checklist (PAGE L/3-1) ]
[ Complete the TIMELINE -> T&D: CSM SEPARATION PREP checklist (PAGE L/3-1) ]
[ Follow the TIMELINE -> T&D: CSM SEPARATION checklist (PAGE L/3-2) to separate at 003:15:20. ]
[ Complete the checklist for TRANSPOSITION, then follow the TIMELINE -> T&D: DOCKING checklist (PAGE L/3-2) to dock before 003:25:00. ]
[ Complete the TIMELINE -> T&D: POST DOCKING checklist (PAGE L/3-4). ]
[ Complete the TIMELINE -> T&D: CM/LM PRESSURE EQUALIZATION checklist (PAGE L/3-5). ]
[ Complete the TIMELINE -> T&D: TUNNEL HATCH REMOVAL checklist (PAGE L/3-5). ]
[ Complete the TIMELINE -> T&D: LM UMBILICAL CONNECTIONS checklist (PAGE L/3-5). ]
[ Complete the TIMELINE -> T&D: HATCH INSTALLATION checklist (PAGE L/3-5). ]
[ Complete the TIMELINE -> T&D: PRE LM SEP & EJECTION checklist (PAGE L/3-5). CSM/LM EJECTION scheduled to 004:09:45 ]
[ Follow the TIMELINE -> T&D: LM SEP & EJECTION checklist (PAGE L/3-6) eject from the S-IVB at 004:09:45 ]
[ Complete the TIMELINE -> T&D: POST LM EJECTION checklist (PAGE L/3-6) ]
[ S-IVB EVASIVE MNVR ]

[ Charge Battery B (TIMELINE -> SYSTEMS 1: EPS -> Battery Charging) - use the Checklists -> (AOH) Command Module -> Mission: Mission Details checklist and follow the lunar coasting schedules for battery charge, purge etc.]
[ Cislunar Navigation - P23]
[ CSM SYSTEMS CHECK: DEACTIVATE PRIMARY EVAP (PAGE S/1-6) ]
[ Use CREW MEMBERS -> Request REFSMMATs -> Request PTC REFSMMAT ]
[ P52, Option 1 (PTC ORIENT) ]
[ Complete a GDC ALIGN to align the GDC with the IMU containing the new PTC ORIENT ]
[ Maneuver to PTC ATT P=90, Y=0]
[ Follow the TIMELINE -> G&C 7 - PTC/ORBRATE -> (V79) ORBRATE/PTC to set up the PTC roll at 0, 90, 0 ]
[ LiOH canister change: A - use the Mission Details checklist to follow the canister change schedule during this mission.]
[ TIMELINE -> SYSTEMS 1 - GENERAL -> PRE-SLEEP CHECKLIST (PAGE S/1-29) ]
[ Rest period: 13:30, 9H, wake up time: 022:30:00 - follow the sleeping schedule from now on.]
[ TIMELINE -> SYSTEMS 1 - GENERAL -> POST-SLEEP CHECKLIST (PAGE S/1-29) ]
[Cislunar Navigation P23]
[ IVT TO LM ]
[ LM FAMILIARIZATION ]
[You have reached the Lunar Sphere of Influence]
[Plan and execute the LOI burn with a target Ap of ~170 nmi and a Pe of ~60 nmi]
[ LOI-1 ignition ]
[ LOI-1 complete ]
[ Plan the LOI-2 circulation burn to reach ~60 nmi x ~60 nmi orbit, and complete the burn]
[ Pressurize the LM, CM/LM Pressure Equalization ]
[Prepare for LM ingress, open LM hatch, IVT to LM]
[Transfer to LM POWER]
[COMM ACTIVATION & testing]
[ COMM DEACTIVATION, TRANSFER TO CSM POWER, LMP TO CSM ]
[ LM FAMILIARIZATION, LM ACTIVATION - UNDOCK AT GET 100:15:00]
[ Plan the DOI burn to land at the Sea of Tranquility, wihth at Pe of ~8.5 nmi ]
[ DOI ignition ]
[ DOI burn complete - request DPI and perform lunar landing. ]
[ Landing complete ]

Title: APOLLO 11 (FLIGHT PLAN)
Description: The crew of Apollo 11 is in the process of preparing the craft for ascent.
